						<summary>

						<p>Front wall of the Veṅkaṭēśa-perumāḷ temple, north side of the entrance.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśivadēva, 1558 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1480 (current), Pingaḷa, Āshāḍha ba. 11,</hi> corresponding to 1558 A.D., July 22, Monday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It records a gift of land by <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Vōbuḷarāja, son of Nandēla Avubhaḷa-rāja to the god Chokkanāthasvāmi of Nelandalūru. However, the details of the gifts are lost. The village Kaḍapa is stated to have been situated in Ghandikōṭa-sīma which was given as <hi rend="italic">nāyaṅkara</hi> to the donor by the king.</p>						

						</summary>
